CatDescriptText: Mrs. Mabel Fitts, housewife, 225 Second Street, Rankin, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 6, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that too much leniency is shown teenagers who commit crimes?" answer reads: "Yes, I do."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mabel Fitts wearing flecked coat and head scarf,  standing in front of pedestrians and shops
